consistent-this.option:
This rule has one or more string options:

- designated alias names forthis(default"that")

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule with the default"that"option:

/*eslint consistent-this: ["error", "that"]*/

let that = 42;

let self = this;

that = 42;

self = this;

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule with the default"that"option:

/*eslint consistent-this: ["error", "that"]*/

let that = this;

const self = 42;

let foo;

that = this;

foo.bar = this;

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule with the default"that"option, if the variable is not initialized:

/*eslint consistent-this: ["error", "that"]*/

let that;
function f() {
    that = this;
}

